AU  - Liu, Qingmin
T1  - Optimal Contracts for Experimentation
PY  - 2016
Y1  - 2016/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdw013
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 83
IS  - 3
SP  - 1040
EP  - 1091
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper studies a model of long-term contracting for experimentation. We consider a principal–agent relationship with adverse selection on the agent’s ability, dynamic moral hazard, and private learning about project quality. We find that each of these elements plays an essential role in structuring dynamic incentives, and it is only their interaction that generally precludes efficiency. Our model permits an explicit characterization of optimal contracts.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdw013
